[SN]TITLE[SN]
Fire at Broadford Works, Aberdeen, 'suspicious'

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A large fire which broke out at a disused factory near Aberdeen city centre is being treated as suspicious by police.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Firefighters were called out to the Broadford Works industrial site on Hutcheon Street at about 18:10 on Saturday.
More than 40 firefighters were at the scene at the height of the fire. No-one was hurt.
Police said they were following a positive line of inquiry.
Residents living near the former textile mill were advised to keep windows shut.
